menu "breadboard: bb_system (routes)"

config BB_SYSTEM_BOOT_BANNER
    bool "Emit a one-time boot banner (project/version/build/idf)"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_system auto-emits a single bb_log_i line during the
        EARLY init tier naming the project, firmware version, build
        date/time, and ESP-IDF version — via the existing bb_system
        accessors. Disable for consumers that build their own boot banner.

config BB_SYSTEM_REBOOT_BUDGET_MIN_INTERVAL_S
    int "Minimum seconds between rate-limited reboots (per cause)"
    default 1800
    range 300 86400
    help
        Shared reboot-budget cooldown consulted by bb_system_reboot_budget_
        allows()/_record() (B1-863). Each bb_reboot_cause_t is rate-limited
        independently (its own persisted ring) but shares this ONE knob —
        at most one reboot per this many seconds, per cause.

config BB_SYSTEM_REBOOT_BUDGET_DAILY_CAP
    int "Maximum rate-limited reboots per rolling 24h (per cause)"
    default 4
    range 1 10
    help
        Hard cap on reboots per cause within a rolling 24h window,
        persisted across reboots (ring buffer of reboot timestamps).

config BB_SYSTEM_BOOT_FAIL_THRESHOLD
    int "Boot-fail count at/above which a caller should treat the device as stuck"
    default 3
    range 1 255
    help
        Consulted by bb_system_boot_fail_over_threshold() (B1-864). Compared
        against bb_system_boot_count_get() with >=. Not wired into any
        reboot call site by this component — a consumer (e.g. the WiFi FSM's
        anti-brick fallback) decides what to do once the threshold is hit.

config BB_SYSTEM_ROUTES_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Build bb_system HTTP routes (/api/version, /api/reboot, /api/ping)"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_system compiles its routes module that exposes
        GET /api/version, POST /api/reboot, and GET /api/ping. Adds bb_http,
        bb_json, and esp_timer to bb_system's PRIV_REQUIRES.
        Disable for headless system-helper-only consumers that don't want to
        drag the HTTP stack.

endmenu
